# Lutherie TODO

## Bugs / Cleanup
- short cables shouldn't curl back on themselves and make the arrow look the wrong direction.
- Ctrl+A to make component menu context menu for convenience
- Spectrum Analyzer labels, have channels naturally add to specialized Analysis Widget. 
- Fix the issue with positioning of the graph panel when docking something
- Create zoom out view of graph panel with drag to navigate
- Create max zoom out of graph panel
- allow group deletions?
- when content deleted from control panel, update geometry so that min size doesn't get messed up
- create specialized widget for midi filter (horizontal piano roll, highlight pass-through key ranges)
  - PianoRollWidget should be renamed to SequencerWidget, and the PianoRoll component should be broken out and given a horizontal/vertical flag.8
- Figure out whatever is happening with oscillator noise
- KDDW dock widgets that aren't on the main window show "gui" in title bar if they are docked together
- request rename when node gets its unique name (so that parameters/other panels update properly)
- Sequencer: 
  - don't allow note adds while status is on. 
  - When status is toggled off, send note-off commands for all active notes, and reset the timer (so when status turned on we start at beginning)

## UI

### Layout
- GraphPanel defaults to central widget but can be docked/moved freely
- Add "open editor" button to ComponentParameters (and node right click context menu) that launches specialized widget as a floating KDDW::DockWidget

### Components
- Expose Min/Max/Default parameters via right click tool window
- Prevent modules from spawning on top of each other
- Move add logic to toolbar menu with hotkeys for quick-add context menu
- Component duplication — plain copy, and copy-with-connections

### Sequencer
- Per-note velocity support
- Shift+scroll for horizontal scrollbar
- Prevent note creation while engine is running
- On sequencer status toggle, send note-off for all active notes (or disallow toggling during run)
- labels on individual notes (midi note + velocity)
- adjust size of sequencer grid based on duration parameter

## Signal Flow

### Control Connections
- create boolean control port signal/trigger system
  - hard sync ( phase cycle complete signal, phase reset trigger)

### Buffer-level Components
- New BufferSource extension of BaseComponent
- New BufferProcessor extension of BaseComponent
- New BufferConnection type
  - Square Port + Dashed Line for visual representation
- Relevant Components:
  - File Reader (no input, buffer output)
  - Recorder (read in and save an audio stream, buffer output)
  - SpectralFilter ( buffer in, buffer out)
  - Chopper ( buffer in, buffer out)
  - BufferTrigger ( buffer in, midi in, stream out )
  - BufferLooper ( buffer in, stream out )

### Macro Knobs
- Macro Knob panel docked to edge of graph panel, moves with it
- Modulation socket on each macro knob
- Macro Edit Mode: indicator appears next to each control panel parameter, drag to assign to macro knob
- Indicator outside of Macro Edit Mode showing a macro is assigned (same style as MIDI indicator)
- Arbitrary functions to apply value from macro knob to control knob, listed below the macro knob
  
### MIDI Control Mapping
- Right click context menu on parameter widget to map to MIDI control
- Continuous variables: generate wiggle to map
- Discrete variables: map on button press count with configurable threshold
- Warn if continuous mode sees no continuous values coming in (and vice versa)
- Indicator on parameter showing MIDI association, hover to reveal control id

### Peripheral Devices
- match audio output to the number of ports on the peripheral device
- allow for multiple midi peripheral devices
- support midi output peripherals
  
